uBiome Microbiome Testing









Citizen Scientist? Check out the uBiome Explorer to learn more about your microbiome.Get sequencedXThe World's First Sequencing-Based Clinical Microbiome TestSmartGut™ is a microbiome screening test that uses advanced DNA sequencing technology to identify key microorganisms in your gut, both pathogenic and commensal.Request your testBenefitsSmartGut™ is a comprehensive screening test, with the most extensive panel of species and genera on the market.Using next generation high-throughput DNA sequencing technology, our test identifies specific pathogens and other microbes in your gut that might be making you feel unwell. We also measure your bacterial diversity and other useful metrics about your microbiome.Symptoms and diagnosesSmartGut is a screening test that can help you monitor your overall gut health regularly. It detects the microorganisms associated with several common gut symptoms, including:Abdominal pain/tendernessConstipationCrohn's disease/Ulcerative ColitisBloatingDiarrheaGasGeneral ScreeningIrritable bowel syndrome (IBS)Request nowWhy test with SmartGutEasy-to-useEasy-to-use sample collection kit, which includes clear, simple instructions and everything you need, including a pre-paid return mailer.ComprehensiveSmartGut includes microorganisms that can only be detected by DNA sequencing.Data-drivenPowered by the world’s largest microbiome database, SmartGut includes unique healthy (normal) microbiome ranges.Simple and mess-freeRequires only a very small sample of fecal matter (just enough to tint a cotton swab) that you can collect and return to us quickly and cleanly.Doctor-orderedOrdered by a physician and processed in our CLIA-certified and CAP-accredited lab to give you the confidence and resources to take action.If you’re a licensed healthcare provider, and would like to learn more about how SmartGut can help you provide better care for your patients, read about the benefits of SmartGut.How the test worksRequest your testRequesting a test is quick and easy process. Click on the link below and we will let you know when it is available in your state. Once a doctor orders your test, we will mail your SmartGut Collection Kit directly to your home.Sample at homeSampling can be done in your own bathroom at home and takes less than two minutes. Swab your toilet paper, put the swab in the tube and shake for a minute. Then, simply place your sample in the pre-paid return mailer and drop it in the nearest mailbox.Access your results onlineOnce we’ve processed your test, we’ll send you a link to our website, where you can download a PDF of your test report. Your doctor also will receive a copy of your results.Request your testYour SmartGut testYour SmartGut Collection Kit includes everything you need to complete your sample in less than two minutes, and in the comfort of your own home.SmartGut sample tubeReplacement sample tube2 sterile swabsSample return bagSmartGut return mailerDetailed clinical reportInfectionsThe presence of specific pathogenic microorganisms in your microbiome can be associated with illness, from diarrhea to sore throat.Gut conditionsYour microbiome might include microorganisms associated with conditions such as irritable bowel syndrome, gas, or bloating. Find out more about the relationship between your gut conditions and your microbiome.Lifestyle and dietSmartGut provides Information on how your lifestyle and diet affect the microorganisms in your microbiome, including probiotics in your gut and associations between your microbiome and weight.Microbiome Diversity ScoreThe SmartGut Microbiome Diversity Score indicates how your microbiome compares to healthy participants from the world’s largest microbiome research dataset.SupportOur customer support team is available by email or phone, and is happy to answer your questions about your test kit, results, and more.Request SmartGutWhat's the difference between SmartGut and Explorer?SmartGut is currently available in certain states onlyWe're working on 